  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Apple AirPods Pro 2 Review</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated June 2026 · 11 min read</div>
      <div class="author">By <a href={`/authors/${authorSlug}`}>{author}</a></div>

      <Image src={heroImg} alt="Apple AirPods Pro 2 wireless earbuds with USB-C charging case on a desk" width={1200} height={600} loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" class="hero-img" />

      <ProductCTACard
        productName={productName}
        brand={brand}
        rating={ratingValue}
        price={bestPrice}
        slug={productSlug}
        editorChoice={true}
      />

      <ReviewMeta
        authorSlug={authorSlug}
        lastUpdated={lastUpdated}
        testingDuration={testingDuration}
        productsTested={productsTested}
      />

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</a></li>
          <li><a href="#pros-and-cons">Pros &amp; Cons</a></li>
          <li><a href="#who-should-buy">Who Should Buy This</a></li>
          <li><a href="#detailed-review">Detailed Review</a></li>
          <li><a href="#comparison">How It Compares</a></li>
          <li><a href="#buying-advice">Buying Advice</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <div class="rating-box">
        <div>
          <div class="score">{ratingValue}<span style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#9a3412">/5</span></div>
          <div class="stars">★★★★★</div>
        </div>
        <div class="label">Our rating after 60 days of commuting, calls, and workouts</div>
      </div>

      <div class="verdict" id="quick-verdict">
        <strong>Quick verdict:</strong> The <strong>Apple AirPods Pro 2</strong> are the best true wireless ANC earbuds for iPhone owners. The H2 chip doubles the ANC performance of the original, Adaptive Transparency is the best of any earbud, and the 6-hour battery per charge is class-leading. At $249 they are expensive, and Android users should look elsewhere — but if you live in the Apple ecosystem, the Pro 2 is the earbud to buy.
      </div>

      <p>Apple launched the original AirPods Pro in 2019 and refreshed it in 2022 with the H2 chip, better ANC, Adaptive Transparency, and a new case. A 2023 update swapped the Lightning port for USB-C to comply with EU regulations. We bought the AirPods Pro 2 with the USB-C case at retail and put it through 60 days of daily use, including commuting, calls, runs, and gym sessions, to see whether the $249 price is justified over the original Pro and over-ear alternatives.</p>

      <p>This is the long-form version of our recommendation. For a comparison against Sony, Bose, and Sennheiser over-ear alternatives, see our <a href="/reviews/best-noise-cancelling-headphones-work/">best noise cancelling headphones for work</a> roundup. If you want the over-ear ANC champion, the <a href="/reviews/sony-wh-1000xm5-review/">Sony WH-1000XM5 review</a> covers the benchmark.</p>

      <h2 id="pros-and-cons">Product Summary</h2>
      <ProductSummary pros={pros} cons={cons} bestFor={bestFor} notFor={notFor} />

      <h2 id="who-should-buy">Who Should Buy This</h2>
      <p>See the summary above for a quick breakdown of who this product is best for and who should skip it.</p>

      <h2 id="detailed-review">Detailed Review</h2>

      <h3>Active Noise Cancellation: The H2 Chip Doubles Down</h3>
      <p>The defining upgrade of the AirPods Pro 2 is the H2 chip, which Apple claims delivers up to 2x better active noise cancellation than the original AirPods Pro (H1 chip). In our testing, the claim holds up. On a six-hour flight, the Pro 2 reduced cabin rumble to a faint whisper — noticeably quieter than the original Pro, and competitive with the Sony WF-1000XM5. The low-frequency cancellation is the biggest improvement; airplane and train engine drone essentially disappear within seconds of turning on ANC.</p>

      <p>In an open office, the Pro 2 erased keyboard chatter and HVAC noise to the point where coworkers had to wave to get our attention. The Pro 2 trails the over-ear Sony WH-1000XM5 and Bose QuietComfort Ultra in raw ANC strength — over-ear headphones have a physical advantage from the ear cup seal — but among true wireless earbuds, the Pro 2 is the best ANC we have tested. The Sony WF-1000XM5 is close, but the Pro 2 edges it out on low-frequency cancellation.</p>

      <p>The ANC controls live in the AirPods settings on iOS, not on the earbuds themselves. You can switch between ANC, Transparency, and Off by long-pressing the stem, but finer tuning requires the phone. This is the Apple way — it is simple if you accept Apple's defaults, and frustrating if you want manual control. There is no dedicated ANC strength slider like Sony and Bose offer.</p>

      <h3>Adaptive Transparency: The Best Transparency Mode on the Market</h3>
      <p>Adaptive Transparency is the Pro 2's standout feature, and it is genuinely superior to every competitor. Standard transparency mode on earbuds pipes in ambient sound through the microphones, so you can hear your surroundings. The problem is that loud sounds — sirens, construction, train brakes — are also amplified, which is uncomfortable and can damage your hearing. Adaptive Transparency uses the H2 chip to dampen sounds above 85 dB in real time, reducing them by up to 15 dB without muffling voices or conversation.</p>

      <p>In practice, this means you can walk down a busy street with Adaptive Transparency on and hear conversations clearly, but a passing siren or a jackhammer is reduced to a tolerable level instantly. It feels like the loud sounds are being turned down by an invisible hand. We tested it on subway platforms, construction sites, and a concert, and it worked flawlessly every time. No other earbud does this — Sony and Bose offer standard transparency, but neither adapts to loud sounds in real time.</p>

      <p>For outdoor running and city walking, Adaptive Transparency is a safety feature as much as a convenience. You hear traffic and people clearly, but you are not startled or hurt by sudden loud noises. We recommend leaving the Pro 2 in Adaptive Transparency mode for any outdoor activity — it is the best combination of awareness and protection available.</p>

      <h3>Sound Quality and Spatial Audio: Bass-Forward but Fun</h3>
      <p>The AirPods Pro 2 use a custom driver and amplifier that deliver a bass-forward, warm sound signature. The low end is punchy and present — bass lines and kick drums have weight and impact that the original Pro lacked. The midrange is clear and forward, which suits vocals and podcasts. The treble is smooth and non-fatiguing, but it lacks the detail and air of the Sony WF-1000XM5 or the Sennheiser Momentum True Wireless 4. If you want neutral, analytical sound, the Pro 2 is not for you — it is tuned for fun, not for fidelity.</p>

      <p>Customizable Spatial Audio is the Pro 2's standout audio feature. Using the gyroscopes in the earbuds and your iPhone, Spatial Audio creates a surround-sound experience with head tracking — the audio stays anchored to your device as you turn your head, creating the illusion of a fixed sound stage. We tested it with Dolby Atmos Music on Apple Music and movies on Apple TV+, and the effect is convincing — it feels like a room of speakers rather than two earbuds. The head tracking is subtle but effective, and it works with any content that supports Dolby Atmos.</p>

      <p>The catch is that Spatial Audio requires an Apple device — it does not work on Android or Windows. If you are on Android, you get standard stereo sound, which is still good but unremarkable. The Pro 2 also supports head-tracked Spatial Audio for FaceTime calls, which makes group calls feel more natural — voices come from the direction of the person speaking on screen.</p>

      <h3>Battery and Case: 6 Hours Per Charge, 30 With the Case</h3>
      <p>Apple rates the Pro 2 at 6 hours of listening per charge with ANC on, and 5.5 hours with ANC and Spatial Audio on. The USB-C MagSafe case provides 4 additional charges, for 30 hours of total battery. In our testing, we averaged 5.5 to 6 hours per charge with ANC on and mixed music and calls — matching Apple's claim. A 5-minute charge in the case gives about 1 hour of listening, which is enough to finish a commute or a workout.</p>

      <p>The battery life is best-in-class for true wireless ANC earbuds. The Sony WF-1000XM5 lasts 8 hours per charge (longer than the Pro 2) but only 24 hours with the case (shorter than the Pro 2). The Bose QuietComfort Earbuds II lasts 6 hours per charge and 24 hours with the case. The Pro 2's balance of 6 hours per charge and 30 hours total is the best overall package for daily commuting.</p>

      <p>The case is small, pocketable, and includes a built-in speaker that plays a sound when you use Find My to locate it — a genuinely useful feature if you misplace your case in a bag or under a couch. The case charges via USB-C (on the 2023 refresh), MagSafe, Qi wireless, or a Lightning cable (on the original 2022 model). The lanyard loop is a nice touch for attaching the case to a bag. After 60 days, the case battery showed no measurable degradation.</p>

      <h3>Fit, Comfort, and IP54: Built for Workouts</h3>
      <p>The Pro 2 keeps the original Pro's stem design, which is polarizing — some users find it comfortable and secure, others find it looks awkward. The fit is excellent for most ears, thanks to the new XS silicone tip that fits smaller ear canals. The original Pro shipped with S, M, and L tips; the Pro 2 adds XS, which fits ears that found the S tip too loose. We tested the XS tip on a tester with very small ear canals and it fit securely — a real improvement over the original.</p>

      <p>The Pro 2 has an IP54 rating for dust and sweat resistance on both the earbuds and the case — a first for AirPods. We tested them on 5K and 10K runs, in the gym, and during high-intensity interval training, and they stayed put without adjustment. The sweat resistance held up — we rinsed the earbuds under a tap after a sweaty run (Apple does not officially recommend this, but it worked) and they functioned perfectly. The case is also IP54 rated, so you can toss it in a gym bag without worrying about sweat damage.</p>

      <p>The ear tip fit test is a mixed bag. The test uses a microphone to check for a proper seal, and it works well for most users. However, with the XS tips, the test was inconsistent — it reported a good seal when the fit was actually loose. We recommend doing a manual fit check (tug on the earbud gently — if it stays, the seal is good) rather than trusting the test entirely with the XS tips.</p>

      <h2 id="comparison">How It Compares to the Competition</h2>
      <p>The Pro 2 competes against the Sony WF-1000XM5, the Bose QuietComfort Earbuds II, and the Samsung Galaxy Buds Pro 3. Here is how they stack up:</p>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Earbud</th>
            <th>Price</th>
            <th>ANC</th>
            <th>Battery (per charge / total)</th>
            <th>Transparency</th>
            <th>Android Support</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>AirPods Pro 2</strong></td>
            <td>$249</td>
            <td>Excellent</td>
            <td>6h / 30h</td>
            <td>Adaptive (best)</td>
            <td>Limited</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Sony WF-1000XM5</td>
            <td>$278</td>
            <td>Excellent</td>
            <td>8h / 24h</td>
            <td>Good</td>
