      <p>The <strong>Sony WF-1000XM5</strong> lasts 8 hours per charge (longer than the Pro 2) and has a more neutral, detailed sound signature with LDAC hi-res support. It has full Android support, including multipoint and an Android app. The trade-off is a less effective transparency mode and a less comfortable fit for small ears. If you are on Android or want the best sound quality, the WF-1000XM5 is the pick — but iPhone owners get more from the Pro 2.</p>

      <p>The <strong>Bose QuietComfort Earbuds II</strong> has ANC that rivals the Pro 2 and a more comfortable fit for large ears. It has full Android support and a dedicated app. The trade-off is a bulky case, weaker transparency, and a less premium feel. At $249 it is a strong alternative if you find the AirPods Pro 2 fit uncomfortable.</p>

      <p>The <strong>Samsung Galaxy Buds Pro 3</strong> is the best option for Samsung Galaxy owners. It has full Android support, a comfortable fit, and good ANC. The sound is tuned for pop and hip-hop, and the case is compact. The trade-off is weaker ANC than the Pro 2 and no Spatial Audio. If you are on Samsung and want a seamless ecosystem experience, the Buds Pro 3 is the pick.</p>

      <h2 id="buying-advice">Buying Advice</h2>
      <p>Buy the Pro 2 if you are an iPhone owner who wants the best true wireless ANC earbuds with seamless ecosystem switching. The H2 chip, Adaptive Transparency, and 6-hour battery make it the best all-rounder for Apple users. If you own an iPhone, iPad, and Mac, the automatic device switching alone justifies the $249.</p>

      <p>Wait for a sale if you can. The Pro 2 drops to $199 around Black Friday and Prime Day, and we have seen it as low as $189 during clearance events. The Pro 2 is rarely out of stock, so patience pays. Apple also runs a Back to School promotion where the Pro 2 is free with an eligible Mac or iPad for students.</p>

      <p>Skip the Pro 2 and buy the Sony WF-1000XM5 if you are on Android. The WF-1000XM5 offers full Android support, longer battery per charge (8 hours), and a more neutral sound — all at a similar price. The trade-off is weaker transparency and a less comfortable fit for small ears. See our <a href="/reviews/best-noise-cancelling-headphones-work/">noise cancelling roundup</a> for the full breakdown.</p>

      <p>Consider the Bose QuietComfort Earbuds II if you find the AirPods Pro 2 fit uncomfortable. The Bose has a more secure fit for large ears and full Android support. The trade-off is a bulky case and weaker transparency. If you want over-ear ANC instead, the <a href="/reviews/sony-wh-1000xm5-review/">Sony WH-1000XM5</a> is the benchmark at $399.</p>

      <p>Buy AppleCare+ if you lose earbuds. The Pro 2 earbuds are small and easy to lose, and a single replacement earbud costs $89 from Apple. AppleCare+ for Headphones ($29 for two years) covers two accidental damage incidents at $29 each, and it is the cheapest insurance against loss. Pair the Pro 2 with a <a href="/reviews/best-usb-c-hub-macbook/">USB-C hub</a> to charge them from your MacBook.</p>

